-- Hungary Plans Monthly Limit for Tax-Free Calls, Index Reports
-- B y   B a l a z s   P e n z
-- 2012-05-02T18:00:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/hungary-plans-monthly-limit-for-tax-free-calls-index-reports.html
Hungary plans to make 10 minutes of
phone calls a month exempt from a proposed tax, the  Index  news
website reported, citing unidentified ruling-party officials.  The exemption is intended to relieve elderly people with
low phone usage, Economy Minister  Gyorgy Matolcsy  told a meeting
of lawmakers from the governing Fidesz party today, according to
Index. The government will limit the monthly tax to 700 forint
($3.25) per person, Index said. The news website Origo reported
the monthly limit earlier today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Balazs Penz in Budapest at 
